  <h2>How to Use the Grocery List Organizer</h2>
  <p>This <strong>grocery list organizer</strong> helps you plan your shopping trips efficiently by automatically sorting items into store aisle categories. Add items one at a time or paste an entire recipe ingredient list to build your shopping list in seconds.</p>
  <h3>Adding Items</h3>
  <p>Type an item into the input box with an optional quantity (e.g., "2 lbs chicken breast" or "bananas"). The organizer automatically detects the aisle category. You can also manually select a category from the dropdown if the auto-detection doesn't match your store's layout.</p>
  <h3>Bulk Import from Recipes</h3>
  <p>Click "Paste recipe ingredients" to open the bulk import area. Paste your recipe's ingredient list — one ingredient per line — and click "Import All." Each ingredient is parsed and categorized automatically, making it easy to go from recipe to shopping list in one step.</p>
  <h3>Shopping with Your List</h3>
  <p>Items are grouped by aisle so you can work through the store section by section without backtracking. Tap the checkbox next to each item as you add it to your cart. Checked items dim and move visually to show your progress. When you're done, use "Remove Checked" to clean up.</p>

  <h2>Smart Features</h2>
  <h3>Duplicate Combining</h3>
  <p>If you add "2 cups milk" and later add "1 cup milk," the organizer combines them into "3 cups milk" — no duplicate entries cluttering your list. This works across recipe imports too, so combining multiple recipes into one shopping list is seamless.</p>
  <h3>Multiple Saved Lists</h3>
  <p>Create separate lists for different purposes — a weekly grocery run, a party prep list, a pantry restock. All lists are saved in your browser's localStorage and persist between sessions. No account needed.</p>

  <h2>Store Aisle Categories</h2>
